<br>
As far as classes casting. . .<br>
I beat a damned 51 ranger at level 41 in pure melee, no spells, head to head. I press autoattack, stand there for awhile. If he had used any spells, I would have been a done! Anyone warrior who limits another class is giving himself the upperhand. It's like telling a Rogue not to backstab! <br>
Asking for no LoH is fairly reasonable. I am a warrior, I am slightly biased I guess, but you are allowed to use it once per day. This is not a skill you can use at any time. They can use all the spells they want, but LoH is a little too much. I beat a level 49 SK at level 47, who HTed me, so I won't argue that I guess.<br>
<br>
<br>
